# Operating manual (read on every task)

## How you work
- Work ONLY within the **capsule** named in the current task (see /docs/capsules/).
  Never edit files outside that capsule's `domain`.
- Never ingest the whole codebase. Load only the files the active capsule needs.
- The active capsule's `constraints` are **absolute laws**. If you cannot satisfy one,
  STOP and report it — do not work around it.
- The source of truth for the data model & workflows is **/docs/spec.md**.
  If a request conflicts with the spec, STOP and ask before coding.
- Do ONLY what the prompt asks. No scaffolding ahead, no out-of-scope refactors,
  no new architectural patterns (event bus, rule engine, extra layers) without asking.
- Keep diffs small. If a change must reach beyond the capsule domain, list a short plan and wait.
- When a business rule is unclear, ASK — never guess.

## Architecture (non-negotiable)
- One PostgreSQL database. No microservices, no DDD bounded contexts, no event sourcing.
- Layering: **router → service → model**.
  Routers handle HTTP only (validation, status codes). ALL business logic lives in services.
  Models are SQLAlchemy only.

## Conventions
- Stack: FastAPI · SQLAlchemy 2.x (typed `Mapped[...]`) · Pydantic v2 · Alembic.
- snake_case columns, plural table names (`people`, `enrollments`).
- Every mutable table has `created_at` and `updated_at` (timezone-aware).
- Enums are declared once and reused; default values match /docs/spec.md.
- **Money:** every monetary field is an **integer in Toman**. Never float, never Decimal.
- All timeline writes go through the single `log_activity` helper — never inline an Activity insert.
- Never return password hashes or secrets in API responses.

## Multi-tenancy (always on)
- Every tenant-owned table has an `org_id` (see /docs/spec.md §8). User carries `org_id`.
- ALL reads/writes are scoped to the current org via the shared scoping helper — never rely on a developer remembering to add the filter per endpoint.
- For v1 there is one organization; set `org_id` automatically from the current user's token.

## Definition of done for a capsule
- Model + Pydantic schemas + service + router implemented inside the domain.
- An Alembic migration generated for any schema change.
- No other entity touched.
- All capsule constraints satisfied; if any can't be, reported instead of bypassed.

